function_call.name: get_risks
function_call.arguments: {"risks":[{"Description":"Incomplete or unclear data on the prevalence of psychological health outcomes.","Impact":"Inaccurate understanding of the psychological health outcomes of the study participants.","Mitigation":"Ensure comprehensive and accurate data collection methods are used.","Technologies":"Data validation and quality control tools.","People":"Researchers, study participants, and organizations involved in data collection.","Owner":"Research team and data collection organizations."},{"Description":"Potential bias in the study participants' reporting of psychological health outcomes.","Impact":"Misrepresentation of the prevalence of psychological health outcomes.","Mitigation":"Implement measures to minimize response bias and ensure confidentiality and anonymity.","Technologies":"Anonymous surveys and statistical analysis techniques.","People":"Research participants, data analysts, and researchers.","Owner":"Research team and data collection organizations."},{"Description":"Risk of misinterpretation of the descriptive statistics of psychological health outcomes.","Impact":"Incorrect conclusions drawn from the statistical data.","Mitigation":"Provide clear documentation of statistical methods and definitions used in the analysis.","Technologies":"Statistical software and data visualization tools.","People":"Data analysts and researchers.","Owner":"Research team and data analysis organizations."}]}
